# Testing

## Structure

| Type | Location | Naming |
|------|----------|--------|
| Unit | `src/**/*.test.ts` | co-located with module |
| Config | `vitest.config.ts` | `@/` alias |

No E2E tests yet. No `__tests__/` directory.

## Template

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from "vitest";
import { isAllowedUpload } from "./validation";

describe("file upload validation", () => {
  it("accepts txt and md extensions", () => {
    expect(isAllowedUpload("notes.txt")).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

## What to test

- ✅ Pure functions: `src/lib/validation.ts`, access rule logic
- ✅ Zod edge cases, markdown/plain import helpers
- ❌ Prisma/DB in unit tests (no test DB wired)
- ❌ Full TipTap editor (client-only, no RTL setup)

## Mocks

No mock framework configured. For access tests, use inline pure functions mirroring `getDocumentAccess` rules (see `validation.test.ts`).

## Commands

```bash
npm test              # vitest run (all)
npm run test:watch    # watch mode
npx vitest run src/lib/validation.test.ts  # single file
```

## Coverage

Not enforced. Prefer meaningful business-rule tests over coverage percentage.
